# Workspace & Brand Cleanup Implementation Plan

This document outlines the planned improvements to the `/dashboard/workspace` page and the enforcement of the new gender-neutral, premium cyberpunk design aesthetic across the codebase. All legacy "boss babe" or "boss" terminology will be strictly avoided and systematically removed.

## 1. Workspace UI/UX Enhancements
The workspace page will be upgraded to feel more premium and engaging without resorting to legacy branding.

- **Component Upgrade:** We will use the standard `Card` and `Button` components but enhance them with our modern cyberpunk design tokens (neon borders, subtle glows, glassmorphism) rather than legacy "boss" components.
- **Advanced Filtering and Sorting:** 
  - Add a dropdown to filter saved templates by category.
  - Add a dropdown to sort templates by "Newest", "Oldest", or "Alphabetical".
- **Workspace Metrics (Engagement):** 
  - Add a stats header at the top displaying: Total templates, Estimated time saved, and Most active category.
- **Enhanced Empty State:** 
  - Make the empty state actionable by suggesting top templates to start with.
- **Template Card Details:** 
  - Show tier and category badges directly on the workspace cards.

## 2. Legacy 'Boss' Branding Removal (Codebase Sweep)
To enforce the gender-neutral design, we will systematically find and replace legacy branding.

- **Component Replacement:** 
  - Identify usages of `BossCard`, `BossButton`, and related CSS classes (e.g., `.boss-card`, `.boss-heading`, `.girlboss-badge`).
  - Replace them with standard `Card`, `Button`, and our updated gender-neutral cyberpunk typography and glow classes.
- **Terminology Purge:**
  - Remove "boss" and "boss babe" language from AI agent system prompts (e.g., `roxy-agent.ts`), gamification titles, and email templates.
  - Replace with professional, empowering, and gender-neutral equivalents (e.g., "Founder", "Leader", "Elite").

